## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="d85ff-107">Esse método é usado em conjunto com o <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> método da <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics> classe.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d85ff-107">This method is used in conjunction with the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> method of the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics> class.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d85ff-108">Determinadas sobrecargas do <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> método chamar um método de retorno de chamada definida pelo aplicativo para descobrir se as sobrecargas devem parar ou continuar a execução desse tipo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d85ff-108">Certain overloads of the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> method call an application-defined callback method of this type to find out if the overloads should stop or continue execution.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d85ff-109">Durante a execução, o relevante <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> sobrecargas frequentemente chamam esse método de retorno de chamada para descobrir se devem parar de desenhar a imagem especificada ou se eles devem continuar a desenhar a imagem.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d85ff-109">During execution, the relevant <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> overloads frequently call this callback method to find out if they should stop drawing the specified image or if they should continue drawing the image.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d85ff-110">O <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImageAbort> método de retorno de chamada pode determinar se deseja continuar ou não com base em um algoritmo escolhido incluído nela, opcionalmente usando os dados passados para ele pelo parâmetro callbackdata.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d85ff-110">The <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImageAbort> callback method can determine whether to continue or not based on a chosen algorithm included in it, optionally using the data passed to it by the callbackdata parameter.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d85ff-111">Por exemplo, um algoritmo pode determinar se a imagem foi rolada fora da tela e sinalizar um cancelamento para o <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> método pare de desenho.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d85ff-111">For example, an algorithm might determine if the image has scrolled off the screen and signal a cancellation to the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> method to stop drawing.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d85ff-112">Uma declaração de usuário desse método de manipulação de eventos deve ter os mesmos parâmetros que o <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImageAbort> declaração de delegado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d85ff-112">A user declaration of this event-handling method must have the same parameters as the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImageAbort> delegate declaration.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="d85ff-113">Este exemplo é uma implementação simples dos <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImageAbort> delegar.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d85ff-113">This example is a simplistic implementation of the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImageAbort> delegate.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d85ff-114">Ele simplesmente verifica se o <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> método tiver passado usando o parâmetro callbackdata de dados.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d85ff-114">It merely checks to see if the <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> method has passed it data using the callbackdata parameter.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d85ff-115">(Alguns <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> sobrecargas têm apenas um `DrawImageAbort` parâmetro e não passar nenhum dado; algumas sobrecargas tem ambos `DrawImageAbort` e `callbackdata` parâmetros e pode transmitir dados.) Se nenhum dado foi passado, retorna `true` para sinalizar para chamada <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> método que ele deve cancelar o desenho.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d85ff-115">(Some <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> overloads have only a `DrawImageAbort` parameter and pass no data; some overloads have both `DrawImageAbort` and `callbackdata` parameters and can pass data.) If no data was passed, it returns `true` to signal to the calling <xref:System.Drawing.Graphics.DrawImage%2A> method that it should cancel the drawing.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d85ff-116">Se os dados eram passados, ele retorna `false` para sinalizar que o desenho deve continuar.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d85ff-116">If data was passed, it returns `false` to signal that drawing should continue.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d85ff-117">Uma implementação desse retorno de chamada de realista envolveria a investigação real de alguns critérios para cancelar ou continuar a execução.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d85ff-117">A realistic implementation of this callback would involve the actual scrutiny of some criteria to cancel or continue the execution.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Private Function DrawImageCallback(callBackData As IntPtr) As Boolean  
     ' Test for call that passes callBackData parameter.  
     If callBackData.Equals(IntPtr.Zero) Then  
         ' If no callBackData passed, abort DrawImage method.  
         Return True  
     Else  
         ' If callBackData passed, continue DrawImage method.  
         Return False  
     End If  
 End Function 'DrawImageCallback  
```  
  
```csharp  
// Define DrawImageAbort callback method.  
 private bool DrawImageCallback(IntPtr callbackdata)  
 {  
    // Test for call that passes callBackData parameter.  
    if(callbackdata==IntPtr.Zero)  
    {  
       // If no callbackdata passed, cancel DrawImage method.  
       return true;  
    }  
    else  
    {  
       // If callbackdata passed, continue DrawImage method.  
       return false;  
    }  
 }  
```
